01:14:46,600 --> 01:14:48,113
And do you know why?

792
01:14:48,440 --> 01:14:55,915
Because its a stupid question asked
by a doubtful and unhappy man.

793
01:14:57,640 --> 01:15:02,200
Forget his question.
You just got to keep playing.

794
01:15:02,200 --> 01:15:05,400
Because if you don't you might end
up like him and let me tell you,

795
01:15:05,400 --> 01:15:09,080
he is no fun. Nobody
knows what we're capable of.

796
01:15:09,080 --> 01:15:12,436
The past does not
always predict the future.

797
01:15:13,520 --> 01:15:16,398
Now that team may have seen
us play before

798
01:15:17,440 --> 01:15:19,237
but they've never
seen us play today.

799
01:15:23,080 --> 01:15:25,548
Am I right? / Yeah.

800
01:15:26,560 --> 01:15:27,800
Am I right?

801
01:15:27,800 --> 01:15:29,080
Yeah.

802
01:15:29,080 --> 01:15:35,030
Well, all right then. Well let's
show them what we can do.

803
01:15:39,920 --> 01:15:43,356
One, two, three. Go Ladders.

804
01:16:27,760 --> 01:16:30,957
Hey, come on. Come over here.

805
01:16:34,760 --> 01:16:40,357
No long faces. That was good.
That was our best game yet.

806
01:16:40,800 --> 01:16:41,869
Shut up, Jim.

807
01:16:51,520 --> 01:16:54,273
Good job, Jimmy.
You make a great coach.

808
01:17:07,200 --> 01:17:10,600
Dear Mom
I don't know where to start,

809
01:17:10,600 --> 01:17:13,433
so I'lljust begin with the
end and work my way back.

810
01:17:15,480 --> 01:17:19,109
I came home because I ran out of
money and had nowhere else to go.

811
01:17:20,560 --> 01:17:23,597
If I'd had any other option,
I would have taken it.

812
01:17:24,960 --> 01:17:28,270
I did not consider the simple fact
of having a place to return a blessing

813
01:17:28,720 --> 01:17:31,996
Instead, I thought of it
as a burden and a symbol of failure.

814
01:17:33,160 --> 01:17:35,879
I'm ashamed to admit that
growing up I pitied you

815
01:17:36,240 --> 01:17:39,480
and what I thought was your naive
belief that our dreams could come true,

816
01:17:39,480 --> 01:17:41,436
simply by virtue of having them.

817
01:17:46,880 --> 01:17:50,714
Because the truth, as I witnessed it,
was something completely different.

818
01:17:55,160 --> 01:17:58,320
The truth actually was that nothing
worked out and no one,

819
01:17:58,320 --> 01:18:00,515
anywhere lived the life they wanted.

820
01:18:07,840 --> 01:18:10,513
But I see now, that it was
me with the naive belief.

821
01:18:11,160 --> 01:18:13,435
I thought if I
resigned myself to disappointment,

822
01:18:13,640 --> 01:18:16,916
at least I'd be better off then
those people who tried and failed.

823
01:18:17,760 --> 01:18:20,115
And I hate myself
for only realizing this now

824
01:18:20,280 --> 01:18:23,716
and for taking and taking from you
without giving anything back.

825
01:18:25,280 --> 01:18:28,955
You are one of the few good peaches in
are one of the few good peaches in

826
01:18:31,280 --> 01:18:35,671
I promise not to waste anymore time
or take your love for granted again.

827
01:18:37,440 --> 01:18:40,637
I love you so much. Jim.

828
01:18:45,040 --> 01:18:48,720
P.S. The money in this
envelope is from Stacy.

829
01:18:48,720 --> 01:18:52,269
I figure he owes you at least this
much for all the snacks he's stolen.

830
01:19:04,960 --> 01:19:07,997
And he's the one who's been sending
drugs through the Fed Ex account.

831
01:19:12,320 --> 01:19:15,232
Promise to call you soon. Jim

832
01:19:39,600 --> 01:19:40,589
Thirsty?

833
01:19:50,520 --> 01:19:51,509
What are you doing here?

834
01:19:53,680 --> 01:19:57,593
Benjamin wanted to apologize to you
for telling you to shut up.

835
01:19:59,680 --> 01:20:00,999
I'm sorry Jim.

836
01:20:01,240 --> 01:20:05,995
That's alright, Benjamin.
How'd you find me?

837
01:20:07,120 --> 01:20:10,556
We stopped by the house
to see you. Your dad told us.

838
01:20:15,400 --> 01:20:16,276
Where you going?

839
01:20:18,120 --> 01:20:21,908
New Orleans. / Great.

840
01:20:25,080 --> 01:20:27,514
Benjamin,
do you want to say goodbye to Jim?

841
01:20:28,880 --> 01:20:29,596
Bye, Jim.

842
01:20:29,720 --> 01:20:31,392
Bye... Benji.

843
01:20:34,800 --> 01:20:37,680
You be good to your mother.

844
01:20:37,680 --> 01:20:40,399
And promise me not to
get too much more apathetic.

845
01:20:41,200 --> 01:20:42,838
At least not until your teens.

846
01:20:42,960 --> 01:20:44,154
Okay.

847
01:21:00,400 --> 01:21:02,630
It never would have
worked out anyway.

848
01:21:09,440 --> 01:21:10,793
Is that your bus?

849
01:21:13,800 --> 01:21:14,869
Yeah.

850
01:21:15,800 --> 01:21:17,438
You better run.

851
01:21:30,000 --> 01:21:31,035
Bye.

852
01:21:31,560 --> 01:21:32,754
Bye, Jim.

853
01:21:54,440 --> 01:21:55,759
Stop that, Benji.

854
01:22:04,280 --> 01:22:05,713
Common lets go.

855
01:22:52,480 --> 01:22:55,278
Mom. Stop the car.

856
01:23:09,760 --> 01:23:10,875
Can I get a ride?

857
01:23:11,840 --> 01:23:12,875
Sure.

858
01:23:48,280 --> 01:23:50,111
I thought you never ran.

